headline: Wynn Resorts price target lowered to $146 from $148 at UBS
summary: UBS lowered the firm’s price target on Wynn Resorts (WYNN) to $146 from $148 and keeps a Buy rating on the shares. Wynn Resorts is transitioning from a development-focused story to one centered on free cash flow generation, with geographically diversified cash flow set to rise after the Al Marjan opening in 1Q27, the analyst tells investors in a research note.
